nd to her representation in art accompanied by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Agnes was born about 1148, in Derbyshire, England, United Kingdom. She married Chaworth about 1175, in Derbyshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"ABT 1148–":"umbes 1148–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1127–Male":"1127–Surnud","1176–Male":"1176–Surnud","1167–1232":"1167–1232","1148–Female":"1148–Surnud","1127":"1127","ABT 1175":"umbes 1175","1148":"1148","1167":"1167","1232":"1232","1176":"1176","ABT 1148":"umbes 1148","Watnall, Nottinghamshire, England":"Nottinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom",", Nottingham, England, Great Britain":"Nottinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Of,, Derbyshire, England":"Derbyshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Of, Derbyshire, England":"Derbyshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"ABT 1148–":"noin 1148–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1127–Male":"1127–Kuollut","1176–Male":"1176–Kuollut","1167–1232":"1167–1232","1148–Female":"1148–Kuollut","1127":"1127","ABT 1175":"noin 1175","1148":"1148","1167":"1167","1232":"1232","1176":"1176","ABT 1148":"noin 1148","Watnall, Nottinghamshire, England":"Nottinghamshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta",", Nottingham, England, Great Britain":"Nottinghamshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Of,, Derbyshire, England":"Derbyshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Of, Derbyshire, England":"Derbyshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"ABT 1148–":"environ 1148–Décédée","–Male":"Décédé","1127–Male":"1127–Décédé","1176–Male":"1176–Décédé","1167–1232":"1167–1232","1148–Female":"1148–Décédée","1127":"1127","ABT 1175":"environ 1175","1148":"1148","1167":"1167","1232":"1232","1176":"1176","ABT 1148":"environ 1148","Watnall, Nottingha